narratives.question_text: What were your expectations for this studio and how well were they met?
comments: I was not entirely sure what to expect but I was happy that you were both receptive to all of our various perspectives. I very much liked doing the research of Havana and was pleased with our site model. All in all I enjoyed the studio but would have liked to have meetings (in some form) twice a week.

Given the compelling prompt, I expected that the studio would more intimately develop arguments for different approaches to housing in Havana. Unfortunately, the studio defaulted to think about housing and design in conventional means. I think that a more exploratory approach would have benefitted the projects and the development of ideas in this studio.The projects would have benefited from outside criticism at points other than mid-review and final. Additionally, the critics should make better attempts to spend equal amounts of time with each student.

All my expectations were met for this studio. I was surprised by how much I enjoyed the method of designing for different sites but also think it would be nice to see different proposals for the same site.
I had high expectations and they were met
